Mount Gilead XC and Track & Field
July 27 at 3:12 PM ¬∑

The Mount Gilead Cross Country and Track & Field teams are hosting a virtual 5k this summer! Grab a friend (or two) and walk, bike, or run a 5k between August 24-30 and support a great cause!

Ready to hear more!? All you need to do to participate is buy a t-shirt from the team store link provided below before August 17. T-shirts can be picked up at the high school track on August 22 from 8am-noon or it can be shipped directly to your home at an extra cost. Once you complete your 5k, email Coach Lauren Huelsman at lhuelsman@mgschools.org a picture of you in your shirt (or favorite MG shirt) and your time so we can share it on our facebook page!

Don't feel you have time to train and be ready to complete a 5k by August 24-30? You can still buy a t-shirt and support our hard working kids. All proceeds will help our student-athletes towards their 2020-21 seasons.

http://www.promoplace.com/tlgraphics/presentation/1014897

Mount Gilead High School
April 18 at 6:02 PM ¬∑

In honor of the graduating Class of 2020, Mount Gilead HIgh School, along with other Ohio Schools, will be lighting up their stadiums to recognize the senior class on Monday, April 20th at 8:20pm.

Though stadiums will remain closed, schools are joining together in solidarity to show support to the seniors and the unexpected changes that have impacted their senior year.

Community members are invited to participate by turning on their porch lights at 8:20pm on Monday.

We know that these unprecedented times have been tough on all students - daily routines being changed, no longer getting to see friends every day, not getting to have then normal classroom learning experience, and no usual spring‚Ä¶

MGHS Swim Team is headed down to OSU to compete in Districts tomorrow!!!! It's a big accomplishment for our itty bitty team. Let's meet at the MG Square to send them off by showing our Purple Pride. Their bus is loading at 10:50am!!!!

All 3 girls relays advanced to districts, as did both boys' free relays. Girls relays contain Madison Hack, Michaela McGill, Taylor Robinson, Cassandra Snopik and Adriana Tinch. Boys relays contain Joel Conrad, Mason Kidwell, Tyler Knight, Eric Mowery and Michael Snopik. Michael Snopik and Joel Conrad also advanced in the individual 50 and 100 freestyle races.

GO INDIANS!!!

Mount Gilead High School Football
January 30 at 6:06 PM ¬∑

The class of 2023, in conjunction with the MGBooster club, are sponsoring a spaghetti dinner on Saturday February 8th from 4-6pm. This dinner will take place at Mount Gilead High School with all the proceeds going to the Stark family. Their son Layne was recently diagnosed with leukemia. We are hoping to help defray some of their medical cost from this benefit dinner. The price for the meal is $10 all checks made payable to MGHS booster club. Dinner will include ; spaghetti,salad,breadsticks,cookies and a drink. If you decide you want to eat at home, we can accommodate carry out orders.
Please help us support one of our fellow Indians in his time of need!
"Just as iron sharpens iron,one man sharpens another!

post_text:
The Mount Gilead Boys Basketball team, recently held a youth basketball camp for 4th, 5th, and 6th graders. The camp focused on offensive and defensive fundamentals, while teaching the campers about teamwork, leadership, competitiveness and good sportsmanship. 25 youth players also participated in a number of competitions, including 1-on-1, 3-on 3, hot shot, free throw, and dribbling competitions. Coach Strasser and Coach Bartlett would like to thank all of the parents for allowing their children to participate and encourage each player to continue to work on their skills. Go Indians!

Pictured Below: Youth Players: Memphis Clapper, Keaton Ayers, Zane Grandstaff, Max Bulkowski, Brycen‚Ä¶

The Mount Gilead Athletic Boosters are in need of people who are enthusiastic, hard working (under pressure) and available to preform all functions of the job descriptions for President and Treasurer.

Job descriptions are as follows:

President:
-Must be able to strategize ways to improve parent/student involvement
-Must be able to run Booster Meetings every 3rd Thursday of each month unless otherwise deemed cancelled for that month
-Must be able to attend the BOE (Board Of Education) meetings
-Must communicate frequently with the Principal/Athletic Director
-Must be able to open concessions on a rotating schedule
-Must attend miscellaneous meetings when necessary and handle any issues‚Ä¶
